Cross-functional cooperation may help create a more cooperative business culture. Create cross-functional teams to work on projects or provide staff from other departments a chance to collaborate. Projects teach workers to trust and cooperate. Reward and acknowledge team accomplishment: Rewarding and recognizing team performance promotes cooperation in the workplace. The corporation should reward teams for their efforts rather than just individuals. Team-building, incentives, and contests may achieve this. Recognizing and praising team accomplishment will encourage collaboration. Encouraging open communication is a third strategy to create a more collaborative workplace. An open-door policy allows employees to discuss problems with supervisors and coworkers. By providing information and updates, the firm can foster transparency. Open communication builds trust and business loyalty. 